divs: Sighting DetailsI stepped out of the backdoor of the storage building at the corner of Ellsworth & Broadway in Denver and when I entered the alley and looked North, I saw a very large grey rectangular object moving on a straight plane, smoothly across the sky from West to East. I looked at it intensely while it was in view and I could not tell what I was looking at - it was unlike anything I've seen before. It looked like it was moving directly over downtown Denver. It was moving at a decent rate and within a few seconds went behind a building in the foreground and I lost sight of it. I didn't see it again. An airplane went by shortly thereafter on about the same route. The object was MUCH larger than the plane I saw just after. As soon as I got in my car I realized I had truly just seen an unidentified flying object especially since I saw a plane after it which looked so completely different in the sky.
